WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.760
All characters and events in this series are fictional
and created solely for entertainment purposes.
Viewer discretion is advised.

00:01:40.560 --> 00:01:43.240
Hello, Hello everyone.

00:01:43.240 --> 00:01:44.360
Hello.

00:01:44.520 --> 00:01:47.759
Hi, Sun. I’m Peach. I’ll be today’s photographer.

00:01:47.759 --> 00:01:50.479
Since when did you get to know that Khun Peach?

00:01:50.479 --> 00:01:51.520
And what about this lipstick?

00:01:51.520 --> 00:01:54.039
I already told you. I’ve never met her before.

00:02:02.800 --> 00:02:04.120
Why are you doing this, P’Flint?

00:02:04.120 --> 00:02:07.160
Why are you suddenly so involved in everything about Sun?

00:02:09.120 --> 00:02:10.240
I made you feel like what?

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:17.040
When we were in the scene together… even the crew were blushing.

00:02:17.240 --> 00:02:19.760
I think once it’s on air, the buzz will be really good.

00:02:20.760 --> 00:02:22.320
Did you get to perform the way we practiced together?

00:02:26.440 --> 00:02:27.240
Like how?

00:02:40.320 --> 00:02:44.360
I’m asking, did you perform it the way we practiced together?

00:02:45.440 --> 00:02:46.320
Like how?

00:03:11.600 --> 00:03:12.800
Nong Sun!

00:03:19.640 --> 00:03:22.520
Let’s save it for later. I’ll teach you then.

00:03:23.360 --> 00:03:24.800
Because if it goes any further…

00:03:26.079 --> 00:03:28.280
I don’t think Sun will need it anymore.

00:03:30.079 --> 00:03:30.920
Excuse me.

00:04:01.120 --> 00:04:02.400
Why did you do that, P’Flint?

00:04:03.520 --> 00:04:04.480
What did I do?

00:04:05.320 --> 00:04:06.160
It's just that you...

00:04:07.000 --> 00:04:08.000
Are you upset?

00:04:11.880 --> 00:04:13.520
I don’t think it wasn't that bad.

00:04:14.720 --> 00:04:18.680
Or was it still not as good as the man you kissed in that scene earlier?

00:04:20.120 --> 00:04:22.600
You don’t have to believe what I say, P'Flint.

00:04:24.920 --> 00:04:26.520
But I want you to know that…

00:04:27.960 --> 00:04:29.040
I’m human too.

00:04:29.720 --> 00:04:30.720
I have feelings.

00:04:31.960 --> 00:04:34.480
I’m not an object that you can do whatever you want to.

00:04:36.040 --> 00:04:37.360
I used to think

00:04:38.200 --> 00:04:39.800
that you would be different from everyone else.

00:04:40.920 --> 00:04:42.520
I guess I was wrong.

00:05:09.760 --> 00:05:12.080
What do we do? She’s not picking up at all.

00:05:12.480 --> 00:05:15.000
And my car keys are in the bag inside Sun’s car.

00:05:15.760 --> 00:05:17.440
Luckily, that you give me a ride.

00:05:19.040 --> 00:05:20.520
P'Flint isn’t answering her phone either.

00:05:20.760 --> 00:05:23.120
And I have a meeting with a client today.

00:05:23.400 --> 00:05:25.520
Why would your sister have to do that?

00:05:25.760 --> 00:05:28.640
Luckily, Nop was the only one who saw it.

00:05:28.960 --> 00:05:31.040
Otherwise, I’d be busy clearing up rumors for sure.

00:05:31.880 --> 00:05:33.880
I’m sorry on behalf of my sister.

00:05:34.720 --> 00:05:37.680
I don’t know why she would do something like that either.

00:05:39.000 --> 00:05:40.040
It's okay.

00:05:45.760 --> 00:05:48.280
She just texted me. she said Sun is already at her condo.

00:05:49.760 --> 00:05:51.960
I should go check on Sun first.

00:05:52.440 --> 00:05:53.159
Sure.

00:05:53.320 --> 00:05:54.680
Hello, Khun Mooham.

00:05:55.960 --> 00:05:56.920
Hello.

00:05:58.920 --> 00:06:00.960
And...what about Sun?

00:06:01.520 --> 00:06:03.720
Hey, how did you get here?

00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:09.200
I should be the one asking you, Khun Fey, how you got here.

00:06:09.920 --> 00:06:13.520
Or is this just another one of your very obvious flirting tricks, Khun Fey?

00:06:14.040 --> 00:06:15.000
Hey!

00:06:15.560 --> 00:06:20.760
Uh… actually, Khun Peach asked Sun to meet today to talk about a photoshoot.

00:06:21.240 --> 00:06:24.320
But I really have to apologize to you, Khun Peach.

00:06:24.520 --> 00:06:26.400
There was a small accident on set.

00:06:26.840 --> 00:06:29.120
That’s why Khun Fey had to come instead of Sun today.

00:06:30.200 --> 00:06:31.200
Photoshoot?

00:06:31.880 --> 00:06:32.640
Yes.

00:06:32.840 --> 00:06:33.800
What kind of photoshoot is it?

00:06:37.880 --> 00:06:41.960
This concept is called We With Memory, or The Colors of Memory.

00:06:42.400 --> 00:06:46.600
It’s a blend of contemporary Thai fashion with vintage locations

00:06:47.840 --> 00:06:50.080
to reflect the changing dynamics of Thai society

00:06:50.480 --> 00:06:54.159
through images that tell a story from the past to the present within a single frame.

00:06:54.520 --> 00:06:57.640
The images will convey the enduring essence of Thai identity.

00:06:57.640 --> 00:07:03.120
While new ideas, courage, and fresh energy are woven in beautifully.

00:07:03.760 --> 00:07:05.480
That sounds really interesting.

00:07:06.160 --> 00:07:10.520
I believe Sun would definitely accept this project.

00:07:15.360 --> 00:07:18.040
I think we shouldn’t rush to any conclusions yet.

00:07:18.600 --> 00:07:21.040
We should review the details carefully before taking on the project.

00:07:21.040 --> 00:07:24.240
Sun’s safety should be our top priority.

00:07:26.040 --> 00:07:31.160
I think it’d be better if you go back and put together the work details
and a new contract first, Khun Peach.

00:07:31.600 --> 00:07:32.560
Then we can discuss it again.

00:07:32.960 --> 00:07:34.960
I’m saying this from a business perspective.

00:07:35.520 --> 00:07:38.200
Because working without clear documentation…

00:07:38.200 --> 00:07:41.240
It doesn’t really look very professional.

00:07:43.520 --> 00:07:45.920
I’m sorry for being so direct.

00:07:46.800 --> 00:07:47.880
Khun Fey.

00:07:57.360 --> 00:08:01.720
I’ve already sent all the documents to Khun Mooham’s email,
in her capacity as the manager.

00:08:05.960 --> 00:08:08.720
However, if you would also like a copy in your capacity as Sun’s friend,

00:08:09.240 --> 00:08:10.320
I can send them to you as well.

00:08:16.920 --> 00:08:20.040
Then… once the documents have been reviewed,

00:08:20.400 --> 00:08:22.680
Let’s arrange another meeting to talk it over, Khun Mooham.

00:08:22.680 --> 00:08:25.680
Actually, I’d prefer to talk to Sun directly.

00:08:25.680 --> 00:08:27.920
Alright. I’ll arrange the meeting for you.

00:08:43.440 --> 00:08:45.440
Why haven't you come back yet?

00:08:46.440 --> 00:08:47.680
I’m actually getting hungry.

00:08:48.800 --> 00:08:50.880
But there’s nothing to eat in your fridge.

00:08:50.880 --> 00:08:52.320
So I bought some for you.

00:08:57.200 --> 00:08:58.280
Thank you.

00:08:59.040 --> 00:09:00.880
Alright… please make yourself comfortable.

00:09:01.600 --> 00:09:02.760
Hold on...

00:09:06.120 --> 00:09:07.320
You’re not hungry?

00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:09.040
No.

00:09:09.520 --> 00:09:11.920
I don’t usually eat late at night.

00:09:13.520 --> 00:09:16.520
That’s okay. I don’t like eating alone.

00:09:17.360 --> 00:09:18.520
I’ll clean it up.

00:09:25.400 --> 00:09:27.400
Where did you get the tea from?

00:09:29.000 --> 00:09:30.280
From the cupboard.

00:09:43.960 --> 00:09:47.280
You actually remember that I like chamomile tea.

00:09:53.200 --> 00:09:54.800
I just bought this box recently.

00:09:55.560 --> 00:09:57.640
It’s not the box I used when I made tea for you before.

00:10:26.760 --> 00:10:28.240
Your bite... It kinda hurts.

00:10:31.080 --> 00:10:33.240
Then why did you kiss me like that in the first place?

00:10:33.760 --> 00:10:35.000
Kiss...

00:10:36.480 --> 00:10:38.320
You call that a kiss?

00:10:44.280 --> 00:10:45.440
This…

00:10:47.600 --> 00:10:48.760
this is a kiss.

00:12:07.320 --> 00:12:08.800
I’m getting tired.

00:12:09.440 --> 00:12:10.520
I’ll excuse myself and go to bed.

00:12:10.800 --> 00:12:12.040
Wait, Sun.

00:12:15.600 --> 00:12:17.200
I…

00:12:19.240 --> 00:12:20.840
What’s going on here?

00:12:20.840 --> 00:12:22.840
Why aren't you guys answering the phone?

00:12:22.840 --> 00:12:25.280
Do you have any idea how worried me and P’Mooham were?

00:12:25.960 --> 00:12:28.320
I left my phone charging in the room.

00:12:30.000 --> 00:12:32.480
I was cooking, so I didn’t hear it.

00:12:33.040 --> 00:12:34.000
Is something wrong?

00:12:35.080 --> 00:12:37.000
You asked me if something was wrong.

00:12:37.160 --> 00:12:39.800
While P’Flint was just standing there, casually cooking?

00:12:40.200 --> 00:12:44.280
But I had to confront that psycho photographer.

00:12:45.760 --> 00:12:47.200
What do you mean?

00:12:47.200 --> 00:12:51.760
I took P’Mooham to meet that Peach to talk about work today.

00:12:53.480 --> 00:12:56.440
I heard she said you have a project with her, Sun?

00:13:05.960 --> 00:13:10.200
At first, I was planning to tell you after you finished filming

00:13:10.600 --> 00:13:13.480
that the meeting tonight is about Peach’s project.

00:13:13.680 --> 00:13:15.240
But something came up first.

00:13:16.080 --> 00:13:21.440
But usually, before P’Mooham agrees to take on any work…

00:13:21.800 --> 00:13:24.000
Aren’t you supposed to tell me first, P’Mooham?

00:13:24.680 --> 00:13:28.920
Why did you accept it this time without telling me at all?

00:13:29.560 --> 00:13:32.440
It was Khun Peach. She reached out through the channel herself.

00:13:33.000 --> 00:13:36.600
So how am I supposed to say no to the channel?

00:13:37.400 --> 00:13:38.840
I understand now.

00:13:40.080 --> 00:13:41.440
As for what happened today…

00:13:42.200 --> 00:13:44.120
Let me explain it to you again, P’ Mooham.

00:13:44.520 --> 00:13:45.760
Okay, Sun.

00:13:50.440 --> 00:13:52.360
Khun Peach contacted the channel directly.

00:13:53.040 --> 00:13:54.680
So P’ Mooham couldn’t turn them down.

00:13:55.280 --> 00:13:57.040
No matter what, I’ll have to work with her on this.

00:13:57.680 --> 00:14:00.000
But you haven’t signed anything with her yet.

00:14:00.760 --> 00:14:04.120
That means you still have the option not to take this job, right?

00:14:05.200 --> 00:14:07.440
At the end of the day, if you really don’t accept it…

00:14:07.600 --> 00:14:10.280
That Khun Peach or whatever. She can probably find someone else to shoot with.

00:14:10.640 --> 00:14:12.400
You don’t need to go meet her.

00:14:13.720 --> 00:14:15.960
Do you want me to get sued by the channel, Fey?

00:14:18.120 --> 00:14:19.560
If you can’t turn it down yourself…

00:14:20.200 --> 00:14:22.200
Just make her choose someone else.

00:14:22.640 --> 00:14:23.720
And that's it.

00:14:34.200 --> 00:14:35.320
P'Flint.

00:14:35.760 --> 00:14:37.760
I have something to talk to you.

00:14:42.040 --> 00:14:45.160
What is it, Fey? I have an early flight tomorrow.

00:14:45.760 --> 00:14:48.720
You didn’t seem to care about your flight when you were in the room earlier.

00:14:49.880 --> 00:14:52.920
I just want to know that everything you did…

00:14:53.640 --> 00:14:54.760
What do you really want?

00:14:55.720 --> 00:14:56.560
What did I do?

00:14:58.680 --> 00:15:01.680
That you were using me as an excuse and staying over at Sun’s condo all night?

00:15:02.520 --> 00:15:05.600
Have the team from the company start meeting at the still photography studio.

00:15:06.560 --> 00:15:08.840
Sending people to interfere with Sun’s drama shoot.

00:15:10.160 --> 00:15:12.640
And on top of that, you kissed Sun today.

00:15:13.800 --> 00:15:16.560
What you did… you may not have thought it through...

00:15:17.120 --> 00:15:18.280
Or didn’t feel anything.

00:15:19.160 --> 00:15:21.160
But Sun might not see it that way.

00:15:23.440 --> 00:15:24.360
I’ll be honest.

00:15:25.680 --> 00:15:27.680
I don’t want Sun to be just a game to you.

00:15:33.720 --> 00:15:36.360
I’m done speaking. Please get some rest.

00:15:38.720 --> 00:15:40.560
When is Sun meeting that photographer again?

00:15:42.480 --> 00:15:43.840
Tomorrow.

00:15:44.800 --> 00:15:46.760
So you’re free tomorrow, right?

00:16:04.240 --> 00:16:05.520
The things you did…

00:16:05.520 --> 00:16:08.040
you may not have thought it through... Or didn’t feel anything.

00:16:09.040 --> 00:16:11.160
But Sun might not see it that way.

00:16:11.600 --> 00:16:12.760
I’ll be honest.

00:16:13.560 --> 00:16:15.560
I don’t want Sun to be just a game to you.

00:16:41.640 --> 00:16:43.120
Here then.

00:17:03.480 --> 00:17:05.720
But there’s nothing to eat in your fridge.

00:17:05.720 --> 00:17:07.200
So I bought some for you.

00:17:15.839 --> 00:17:18.079
In case you need something to drink when work gets tiring.

00:17:18.079 --> 00:17:22.319
Take care of yourself, so your body doesn’t get any weaker.

00:17:27.119 --> 00:17:30.200
You’re waiting downstairs already, right? I’m on my way down.

00:17:40.920 --> 00:17:43.240
You really don’t have to come pick me up.

00:17:43.240 --> 00:17:45.920
P’ Mooham is coming with me anyway.

00:17:46.400 --> 00:17:48.160
I don’t want to trouble you for nothing.

00:17:49.200 --> 00:17:51.760
My sister probably thinks I have nothing better to do

00:17:52.320 --> 00:17:55.080
I just closed a major deal. I thought I’d finally get some rest.

00:17:55.520 --> 00:17:58.080
At this point, I’m basically your secretary.

00:17:58.080 --> 00:18:00.080
I guess she really doesn’t trust me.

00:18:00.480 --> 00:18:03.040
That’s why she sent you to keep an eye on me like this.

00:18:03.640 --> 00:18:07.240
At least she didn’t come in person like last time.

00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:09.760
Who said she’s not coming?

00:18:17.120 --> 00:18:18.240
I agree with you.

00:18:18.240 --> 00:18:21.760
This is a great opportunity for Sun to gain recognition

00:18:21.760 --> 00:18:24.280
as a versatile artist as well.

00:18:24.280 --> 00:18:25.960
Um... Yes.

00:18:27.040 --> 00:18:28.360
Right here.

00:18:33.360 --> 00:18:35.000
Hello. P'Peach

00:18:35.440 --> 00:18:38.440
I’m sorry, there are quite a lot of us.

00:18:40.360 --> 00:18:43.800
That’s perfectly fine. Khun Mooham already informed me.

00:18:45.840 --> 00:18:47.840
Please make yourself comfortable.

00:18:47.840 --> 00:18:49.000
Khun Fey.

00:18:49.680 --> 00:18:50.920
Khun Rafah.

00:18:53.560 --> 00:18:55.560
Shall we get started?

00:18:56.040 --> 00:18:57.640
Please take a look at the slides.

00:18:58.520 --> 00:19:03.640
This project was done for Courage Gallery I worked for, in New York.

00:19:03.960 --> 00:19:06.720
They’re currently looking for an Asian model.

00:19:07.160 --> 00:19:10.480
Not just pretty, but someone who can express a narrative.

00:19:10.480 --> 00:19:12.760
That’s why I think you’d be a great fit for this project.

00:19:12.760 --> 00:19:14.520
So I put your name forward.

00:19:14.520 --> 00:19:17.280
But you already have quite a reputation, don't you?

00:19:17.280 --> 00:19:22.160
You could probably find a model or actress
who’s more established in the global market than she is.

00:19:22.160 --> 00:19:23.920
So why did you choose her?

00:19:26.720 --> 00:19:28.520
Because when I look through the lens…

00:19:28.520 --> 00:19:32.520
What I see in Sun isn’t just her image or her reputation.

00:19:32.520 --> 00:19:36.520
It’s her eyes , the kind that can tell a story without saying a word.

00:19:38.840 --> 00:19:41.080
Even though I have connections…

00:19:41.400 --> 00:19:45.400
I don’t put names forward unless the person is genuinely right for the project.

00:19:49.040 --> 00:19:53.000
Thank you so much for believing in me.

00:19:53.000 --> 00:19:54.640
In a way others never did.

00:19:56.200 --> 00:19:58.000
I’d like to accept this project.

00:19:59.720 --> 00:20:02.160
So, would you be free tomorrow?

00:20:02.680 --> 00:20:06.280
The client would also like to do a fitting and block the shots on location.

00:20:06.840 --> 00:20:10.640
I’d like you to come along so you can have a clearer idea of the project.

00:20:11.280 --> 00:20:12.560
She has work scheduled tomorrow.

00:20:16.160 --> 00:20:19.720
If Sun's not available, Fey can go instead.

00:20:21.840 --> 00:20:23.440
Their sizes are quite similar,

00:20:24.040 --> 00:20:25.320
except for the height.

00:20:28.520 --> 00:20:29.520
Please take care of it, Fey.

00:20:35.480 --> 00:20:36.320
Sun.

00:20:37.240 --> 00:20:40.320
It’s already noon. Would you like to grab lunch together?

00:20:41.000 --> 00:20:42.200
You too, Khun Mooham.

00:20:43.240 --> 00:20:45.240
I’ll have to excuse myself.

00:20:45.520 --> 00:20:48.840
I just got a call from the wardrobe shop asking me to pick up Sun’s outfit.

00:20:49.080 --> 00:20:50.720
Maybe next time, Khun Peach.

00:20:51.200 --> 00:20:53.200
What about you, Sun?

00:20:53.600 --> 00:20:56.560
I hope you won’t turn me down a second time.

00:20:56.880 --> 00:20:59.080
I’d be pretty crushed.

00:21:02.040 --> 00:21:03.160
Sure thing.

00:21:04.680 --> 00:21:06.040
I’m actually pretty hungry.

00:21:09.120 --> 00:21:10.320
Right? Fey.

00:21:10.320 --> 00:21:11.320
Yes?

00:21:13.880 --> 00:21:16.360
Yes. we're pretty hungry.

00:21:18.160 --> 00:21:19.360
Let's go.

00:21:20.040 --> 00:21:21.480
Then let’s meet at the restaurant.

00:21:22.000 --> 00:21:23.360
I’ll send you the location on LINE.

00:21:36.680 --> 00:21:38.440
Maybe… don’t drive for a while.

00:21:54.400 --> 00:21:55.360
Oh my!!

00:21:55.800 --> 00:21:59.440
I’m sorry, I didn’t see the car coming.

00:21:59.880 --> 00:22:01.920
I’ll call the insurance company right away.

00:22:02.280 --> 00:22:05.760
I’m fine. It’s nothing. I can still drive.

00:22:06.360 --> 00:22:08.560
We should hurry, or Sun will be waiting.

00:22:23.920 --> 00:22:25.000
That’s not okay.

00:22:25.400 --> 00:22:28.160
I was raised to believe that if you make a mistake, you take responsibility for it.

00:22:28.720 --> 00:22:30.720
I have to call the insurance, no matter what.

00:22:40.280 --> 00:22:43.680
Is it really necessary to share personal LINE contacts just for work?

00:22:44.600 --> 00:22:48.560
I didn’t give it to her. She probably got my contact from P'Mooham.

00:22:49.680 --> 00:22:52.760
Then I think I’ll need to speak with your personal manager.

00:22:53.360 --> 00:22:56.000
That she shouldn’t be giving out your personal LINE contact so freely.

00:22:58.200 --> 00:23:02.640
If this weren’t about work, I’d understand that you’re just worried about me.

00:23:14.360 --> 00:23:16.360
Hey Fey, did you arrive already?

00:23:19.160 --> 00:23:20.320
What!?

00:23:22.120 --> 00:23:23.440
Okay. Okay.

00:23:24.160 --> 00:23:26.520
Okay then, I’ll see you at the apartment.

00:23:30.520 --> 00:23:34.280
Fey called and said she accidentally hit the back of P'Peach’s car.

00:23:34.720 --> 00:23:38.640
They’re dealing with the insurance right now,
so they probably won’t be able to join us for lunch.

00:23:39.880 --> 00:23:41.240
That’s odd.

00:23:41.880 --> 00:23:44.040
She has never been in a car accident before.

00:23:45.480 --> 00:23:47.200
Maybe she didn’t see it in time.

00:23:48.360 --> 00:23:53.640
Well… how about I take you to grab something to eat and we eat at your place?

00:23:54.080 --> 00:23:55.320
So you can get some rest too.

00:23:55.720 --> 00:23:56.360
Okay.

00:24:06.960 --> 00:24:11.640
If it weren’t for you, I wouldn’t have done this. It’ll ruin my perfect record.

00:24:23.760 --> 00:24:25.280
What would you like to eat, Sun?

00:24:26.240 --> 00:24:28.240
Whatever you’d like.

00:24:33.360 --> 00:24:36.080
It really is you, Sun! May I take a photo with you?

00:24:36.080 --> 00:24:37.000
Sure.

00:24:37.000 --> 00:24:37.760
Let me hold it for you.

00:24:53.240 --> 00:24:55.080
Excuse me, are you Rafah?

00:24:55.440 --> 00:24:56.360
Yes?

00:24:56.600 --> 00:24:59.360
I just watched the show you were a guest on last night.

00:24:59.800 --> 00:25:03.080
As a powerful female CEO, you’re truly my idol.

00:25:03.680 --> 00:25:05.120
Can I take a photo with you?

00:25:06.400 --> 00:25:07.520
Sure thing.

00:25:07.880 --> 00:25:09.280
May I..

00:25:10.040 --> 00:25:11.240
Thank you so much.

00:25:27.920 --> 00:25:29.920
Do you really think this will work?

00:25:30.800 --> 00:25:33.120
I think we could just go back and order delivery at your place.

00:25:34.280 --> 00:25:38.280
Who are you? Why are you wearing glasses and a hat?

00:25:38.840 --> 00:25:40.520
I don’t recognize you at all.

00:25:44.000 --> 00:25:45.480
Shall we go?

00:25:56.240 --> 00:25:58.240
P'Flint.

00:26:03.480 --> 00:26:06.280
What if someone takes a photo and it ends up in the news?

00:26:06.280 --> 00:26:07.960
You can’t blame me.

00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:12.960
Um… who are you? I don’t recognize you at all.

00:26:15.160 --> 00:26:16.640
Let's go.

00:26:21.120 --> 00:26:22.480
It looks like there’s something over there too.

00:26:22.480 --> 00:26:23.520
Yes ma'am.

00:26:36.880 --> 00:26:38.400
Please take care of Peach’s car.

00:26:39.200 --> 00:26:40.840
Yes, Khun Paabfah.

00:26:42.320 --> 00:26:45.200
If there’s anything else you’d like us to check, please let the staff know.

00:26:45.680 --> 00:26:47.120
I’ll head off now.

00:26:47.440 --> 00:26:49.120
Oh. wait a second.

00:26:50.400 --> 00:26:52.280
Khun Fey, you broke my car.

00:26:52.760 --> 00:26:54.560
So you expect me to drive back myself?

00:26:54.880 --> 00:26:57.720
But you just said the car can still be driven. We can file a claim later.

00:26:58.120 --> 00:26:59.840
Then go ahead and drive.

00:27:00.200 --> 00:27:02.840
No. I’ve changed my mind.

00:27:04.200 --> 00:27:07.440
Please inform the service center to arrange a tow truck.

00:27:07.440 --> 00:27:08.520
Sure.

00:27:10.960 --> 00:27:12.960
From today on.

00:27:13.280 --> 00:27:17.480
You’ll have to pick me up and drop me off until my car is fixed.

00:27:22.040 --> 00:27:26.120
That won’t be a problem, will it… my dear counterparty?

00:27:40.040 --> 00:27:44.120
You really didn’t have to buy this much, P’Flint.

00:27:46.240 --> 00:27:48.560
I saw that your fridge only has frozen food.

00:27:48.560 --> 00:27:50.560
Eating like this too often isn’t good for your health.

00:27:51.800 --> 00:27:54.800
I just don’t really have much time to cook.

00:27:55.560 --> 00:27:57.840
By the time I get off work and go home, it’s already late.

00:27:58.320 --> 00:28:00.840
That’s why P'Mooham bought some easy stuff and stocked it for me.

00:28:02.680 --> 00:28:04.280
Let me give you a hand.

00:28:04.280 --> 00:28:05.280
Here.

00:28:22.320 --> 00:28:24.320
Fey messaged me

00:28:24.320 --> 00:28:28.920
saying she’ll likely be late tonight or she might not come in.

00:28:28.920 --> 00:28:31.880
If you’ve finished eating, you can head back first, P’Flint.

00:28:38.480 --> 00:28:42.120
I think… I’ll stay and wait for Fey.

00:28:42.280 --> 00:28:46.600
You said the same thing last time that you’d wait for Fey until morning.

00:28:46.600 --> 00:28:48.680
But this time…

00:28:48.680 --> 00:28:50.680
That excuse won’t work anymore.

00:28:56.280 --> 00:28:59.640
Then… could I stay in you room tonight?

00:29:13.360 --> 00:29:15.120
Are you still working, P’Flint?

00:29:30.280 --> 00:29:32.440
Here, let me help.

00:29:40.840 --> 00:29:44.240
When I have a lot of shoots and my eyes get really tired.

00:29:44.240 --> 00:29:45.800
I’ll do it like this.

00:29:46.720 --> 00:29:48.280
Please close your eyes, P’Flint.

00:29:58.800 --> 00:30:04.680
Doing this will help you relax and ease the tension in your muscles.

00:30:14.600 --> 00:30:16.600
How do you feel?

00:31:53.080 --> 00:31:56.680
I’ve never done it, actually.

00:32:11.760 --> 00:32:15.360
Then, this is okay for you, right?

00:33:09.520 --> 00:33:11.520
When did you go back?

00:33:23.280 --> 00:33:26.760
How come you never answer my calls, Sun?

00:33:27.120 --> 00:33:31.000
Good morning, P’Mooham. What’s going on? You’re here so early.

00:33:31.920 --> 00:33:35.520
Morning? It’s already past ten, Sun.

00:33:35.960 --> 00:33:39.760
Don’t tell me you slept in because…

00:33:42.400 --> 00:33:47.240
Hey! Sun, what happened to your neck? Why is it so red?

00:33:50.280 --> 00:33:51.600
It’s that red?

00:34:04.160 --> 00:34:07.400
I’m sorry. I didn’t mean to.

00:34:20.800 --> 00:34:23.040
You mean… right here?

00:34:27.280 --> 00:34:30.679
So… what brings you here so early, P’Mooham?

00:34:31.480 --> 00:34:36.800
Last night, an anonymous account leaked photos of you with a man at a club.

00:34:40.560 --> 00:34:43.280
I just found out this morning.

00:34:43.280 --> 00:34:45.320
Because the channel contacted me about it.

00:34:45.320 --> 00:34:47.320
So I had to come see you right away.

00:34:49.400 --> 00:34:50.880
I didn’t expect that…

00:34:51.440 --> 00:34:53.920
to face something even more shocking.

00:34:55.800 --> 00:35:00.040
Yesterday, after we separated, I spent the entire day with P’Flint.

00:35:00.560 --> 00:35:02.800
Then how could photos like that even come out?

00:35:03.480 --> 00:35:06.800
Actually, it was more like the whole night.

00:35:09.800 --> 00:35:12.120
Do you think you should speak to the media?

00:35:12.480 --> 00:35:15.040
Just make it clear that the person in the photo is definitely not you.

00:35:15.400 --> 00:35:19.240
We can say that you had work at the company until late.

00:35:19.720 --> 00:35:22.760
I’ll have the legal team issue a letter to confirm it.

00:35:23.520 --> 00:35:25.840
Confirming it won’t really change anything, Khun Rafah.

00:35:25.840 --> 00:35:29.200
The account that posted it doesn’t confirm a clear timeline.

00:35:29.680 --> 00:35:33.000
People could argue that the photos might not even be from yesterday.

00:35:33.160 --> 00:35:36.440
So… what should we do now?

00:35:40.000 --> 00:35:42.000
I’ll have someone look into it.

00:35:42.600 --> 00:35:44.960
The IT team should be able to trace the source of the post.

00:35:46.360 --> 00:35:49.400
I’d like to ask you to look after Sun especially today.

00:35:49.840 --> 00:35:52.960
Because I don’t like people messing with what’s mine.

00:35:54.200 --> 00:35:55.480
Okay.

00:35:59.360 --> 00:36:01.360
I’ve got a flight for work today.

00:36:02.120 --> 00:36:03.720
Be a good girl, okay?

00:36:22.240 --> 00:36:23.600
Here.

00:36:25.040 --> 00:36:26.680
Thank you so much, P'Mooham.

00:36:30.280 --> 00:36:34.080
I think… you can still see some redness on the left side.

00:36:34.560 --> 00:36:36.080
We might need to cover it up a bit more.

00:36:36.840 --> 00:36:38.480
Here, let me help you.

00:36:41.280 --> 00:36:44.960
I won’t ask what happened last night.

00:36:45.480 --> 00:36:47.480
And I won’t stop you either, Sun.

00:36:48.640 --> 00:36:53.640
Because I believe it was partly your choice too, Sun.

00:36:55.000 --> 00:36:58.320
But Flint and I really didn’t cross any lines.

00:37:00.040 --> 00:37:01.080
Sun.

00:37:01.880 --> 00:37:07.280
I’ve been taking care of you since you were too shy to even look straight at the camera.

00:37:08.280 --> 00:37:11.360
How could I not know how you feel, Sun?

00:37:15.280 --> 00:37:16.600
But can I ask you something?

00:37:16.600 --> 00:37:21.120
Don’t let your feelings move faster than what you can handle.

00:37:21.760 --> 00:37:25.320
I’m saying this because I’m worried about you, Sun.

00:37:25.320 --> 00:37:27.560
When we choose to love someone…

00:37:28.720 --> 00:37:32.720
We should be sure they love us the same way.

00:37:33.480 --> 00:37:37.160
Not just something we tell ourselves that we’re being loved.

00:37:39.760 --> 00:37:41.760
Do you understand what I mean, right?

00:37:58.880 --> 00:38:00.000
Thanks.

00:38:01.040 --> 00:38:03.000
- Careful, it’s hot.
- Thank you.

00:38:07.600 --> 00:38:10.840
So how much longer do I have to stay like this, Ms. Photographer?

00:38:11.760 --> 00:38:14.040
I don’t have that much free time.

00:38:15.640 --> 00:38:18.560
Until we get a usable shot.

00:38:19.160 --> 00:38:23.800
Or you can wait until you get bored and just walk away.

00:38:25.320 --> 00:38:29.480
But I’m not Sun… I’m only here as a replacement.

00:38:29.480 --> 00:38:34.400
Just take enough shots to get the angles. You don’t have to be that detailed.

00:38:34.840 --> 00:38:36.840
Because if I have to wait until you’re satisfied…

00:38:37.760 --> 00:38:40.440
am I supposed to stand here posing all day?

00:38:40.440 --> 00:38:43.320
It’s just that I’m not someone who does sloppy work.

00:38:43.720 --> 00:38:46.280
And besides, even if you don’t take the shot…

00:38:46.800 --> 00:38:48.800
You still won’t be able to go home anyway.

00:38:49.080 --> 00:38:52.800
Because you have to wait for me to finish work and then take me home.

00:38:53.280 --> 00:38:56.240
Have you forgotten already, my dear opponent?

00:38:58.400 --> 00:38:59.960
Hey, you.

00:39:03.160 --> 00:39:04.320
Thank you.

00:39:09.520 --> 00:39:11.800
Hey, smile a bit. Don’t look so grumpy

00:39:14.480 --> 00:39:16.360
or you won’t make it home tonight.

00:39:16.360 --> 00:39:18.280
Come on, give me a pretty smile.

00:39:19.000 --> 00:39:21.960
After finishing one set of shots,
we still have to wait almost an hour for the lights to be set up.

00:39:21.960 --> 00:39:23.560
When is this ever going to be done?

00:39:24.400 --> 00:39:28.360
Oh my god, P'Flint… Why does it always have to be me?

00:39:36.720 --> 00:39:39.160
Ice-cream! Please, wait for me!

00:39:41.600 --> 00:39:43.000
How much is it per cup?

00:39:43.000 --> 00:39:44.400
25 baht.

00:39:49.360 --> 00:39:50.520
How much for all of them?

00:39:51.880 --> 00:39:53.160
2,000 baht.

00:39:53.880 --> 00:39:55.720
Then I’ll take all of them.

00:39:55.720 --> 00:39:57.000
Sure thing.

00:40:01.800 --> 00:40:04.120
Have as much as you want. It’s on me.

00:40:04.600 --> 00:40:06.600
Yayy!

00:40:09.560 --> 00:40:12.800
Hurry up and eat it—it’s going to melt! Hurry, it’ll melt!

00:40:27.120 --> 00:40:30.520
Didn’t you say we still had more shooting? Why are you packing up already?

00:40:31.880 --> 00:40:34.400
I already got the shots I needed.

00:40:35.080 --> 00:40:37.280
Didn’t you say yourself that it didn’t have to be too detailed?

00:40:39.480 --> 00:40:41.440
Or if you want to keep shooting, we can.

00:40:41.440 --> 00:40:43.840
No. If it works, it works.

00:40:44.600 --> 00:40:46.120
I’ll go get changed.

00:40:48.920 --> 00:40:52.080
And then you go around saying you don’t like doing sloppy work.

00:40:56.080 --> 00:40:57.760
And who said it was sloppy?

00:41:18.560 --> 00:41:20.840
Sun’s here.

00:41:23.600 --> 00:41:25.600
Wow, you look gorgeous.

00:41:26.920 --> 00:41:29.840
Thank you so much, P’Ae and everyone on the team, for being so kind to me.

00:41:30.960 --> 00:41:34.600
With you being this adorable, how could we not adore you?

00:41:34.600 --> 00:41:35.880
That's right.

00:41:36.480 --> 00:41:39.120
P’Mooham, could you help take some photos and keep them for me, please?

00:41:39.120 --> 00:41:39.960
Sure.

00:41:39.960 --> 00:41:41.280
Please.

00:41:42.840 --> 00:41:44.840
Take nice ones, okay?

00:41:44.840 --> 00:41:46.840
Let’s take some photos.

00:41:53.920 --> 00:41:57.320
Hey, guys. how can we take photos without the male lead?

00:41:59.520 --> 00:42:02.000
Come here, Nop. Let’s take some photos.

00:42:03.800 --> 00:42:05.800
Move a little closer, please.

00:42:13.640 --> 00:42:16.880
Oh, sorry! Could we join you for a photo too, please?

00:42:17.320 --> 00:42:19.320
May I join you for a photo?

00:42:19.320 --> 00:42:20.440
Excuse me.

00:42:20.440 --> 00:42:22.200
May I join you for a photo?

00:42:22.960 --> 00:42:26.680
I just found out that the crew invited you two to the wrap-up party today.

00:42:26.960 --> 00:42:28.520
I heard you were only supposed to shoot one scene, right?

00:42:28.920 --> 00:42:34.400
Exactly. I really have to thank this crew for not being classist like some others.

00:42:34.400 --> 00:42:37.360
They show respect to the actors, but look down on the extras.

00:42:40.520 --> 00:42:43.520
Let’s take some photos so we can get to the party afterward.

00:42:43.520 --> 00:42:45.520
Yes. let’s take some photos.

00:42:45.520 --> 00:42:47.520
One. Two. Three.

00:42:48.120 --> 00:42:50.120
One. Two. Three.

00:42:50.800 --> 00:42:52.800
That’s a wrap.

00:42:53.840 --> 00:42:57.720
Sun, someone sent flowers to congratulate you.

00:42:58.800 --> 00:43:00.640
Thanks a lot.

00:43:02.880 --> 00:43:04.880
The flowers are so beautiful.

00:43:06.080 --> 00:43:08.080
I wonder who sent these.

00:43:08.600 --> 00:43:14.680
It’s nothing, really.
The company where I’m a brand ambassador sent them to congratulate me.

00:43:15.160 --> 00:43:17.160
Let’s continue taking photos.

00:43:22.400 --> 00:43:23.960
Oh! P’Mooham.

00:43:27.400 --> 00:43:31.200
Time really flies. Before we knew it, we’d already finished shooting.

00:43:36.560 --> 00:43:40.920
If I don’t have to come to set next week, I’m really going to miss you a lot, Sun.

00:43:41.840 --> 00:43:47.120
I heard you has filming scheduled for Monday through Wednesday, right?

00:43:47.600 --> 00:43:48.840
What’s there to miss?

00:43:49.640 --> 00:43:52.240
Honestly, P’Mooham, whoever I’m acting with

00:43:52.240 --> 00:43:55.000
The fans don’t ship it as much as when I act with Sun.

00:43:55.400 --> 00:43:59.080
Otherwise, do you think we’d have won “Rising Ship of the Year”?

00:44:01.400 --> 00:44:02.960
Is that really true?

00:44:04.960 --> 00:44:07.560
P’Nop, about what happened that day…

00:44:07.560 --> 00:44:09.360
I haven’t told the channel yet.

00:44:09.360 --> 00:44:11.440
And I haven’t told anyone else either.

00:44:11.440 --> 00:44:13.400
Because I don’t want you to get into trouble.

00:44:16.160 --> 00:44:17.400
Thank you so much

00:44:19.400 --> 00:44:23.640
Then how about we swap the thank-you for a drink with me instead?

00:44:26.680 --> 00:44:29.160
Actually, she doesn't drink.

00:44:29.160 --> 00:44:32.920
This glass is just for Sun to hold, for manners’ sake.

00:44:32.920 --> 00:44:36.000
I’ll drink it for you. I’m good with alcohol.

00:44:37.840 --> 00:44:40.280
P’Mooham, it’s only one drink.

00:44:40.280 --> 00:44:41.600
It should be fine, right?

00:44:42.240 --> 00:44:43.640
Isn’t that right, Sun?

00:44:56.800 --> 00:44:59.000
Bangkok to Hong Kong is only about two hours, right?

00:44:59.360 --> 00:45:04.880
Alright. Try to get here quickly, okay? Don’t bail.
We don’t get to have a full team meet-up like this very often.

00:45:04.880 --> 00:45:09.160
Yeah, I know. I’m on my way. See you at the restaurant.

00:45:16.920 --> 00:45:20.520
Thank you for the flowers and the card, my guardian.

00:45:29.000 --> 00:45:30.640
You’re drinking too?

00:45:36.000 --> 00:45:37.080
Sun.

00:45:38.480 --> 00:45:40.480
Where are you going?

00:45:40.880 --> 00:45:43.000
I need to step out for a moment.

00:45:43.000 --> 00:45:46.840
So I wanted to ask you, P’Mooham, to let the crew know that I might have to leave early.

00:45:46.840 --> 00:45:50.200
Are you rushing back to see Khun Rafah now, Sun?

00:45:52.600 --> 00:45:56.240
I’ve warned you, Sun. I hope you’ll think carefully before making a decision.

00:45:56.840 --> 00:46:02.640
It’s not like that. You know she’s not around. She's working in Hong Kong.

00:46:02.640 --> 00:46:06.160
Fine then. At least Nop will finally stop hanging around you.

00:46:06.480 --> 00:46:09.680
Then you should head back, Sun. I’ll let the crew know.

00:46:09.680 --> 00:46:11.400
Thank you so much, P'Mooham.

00:46:16.760 --> 00:46:17.840
This way, please.

00:46:18.040 --> 00:46:21.280
Oh, Flint! I thought you weren’t coming.

00:46:23.080 --> 00:46:24.720
How have you been lately?

00:46:25.440 --> 00:46:28.480
Pretty busy. I just flew back from Hong Kong.

00:46:28.480 --> 00:46:29.960
Excuse me.

00:46:35.200 --> 00:46:37.520
We’ve been talking so long we ran out of things to say.

00:46:38.320 --> 00:46:41.240
How could I not come? We don’t get to see each other that often.

00:46:42.160 --> 00:46:43.440
Yeah, true.

00:46:43.760 --> 00:46:49.200
Alright, cheers. It’s such a struggle to get you on the schedule, Khun Rafah.

00:46:49.560 --> 00:46:52.600
Right? Your schedule’s so packed, I thought you were a top celebrity.

00:46:53.160 --> 00:46:54.600
You guys are exaggerating.

00:46:55.200 --> 00:46:58.600
As if you guys are free. I see you flying around all the time.

00:46:58.880 --> 00:47:02.320
Hey, it’s not like you’re the only one running a business.

00:47:02.920 --> 00:47:04.320
Come on, cheers!

00:47:41.000 --> 00:47:44.200
Hey, Flint, aren’t you going in?

00:47:45.400 --> 00:47:46.760
I’ll be right back.

00:48:05.880 --> 00:48:07.240
Excuse me, could you move aside, please?

00:48:08.000 --> 00:48:09.960
I thought you said you were going to the wrap party.

00:48:11.200 --> 00:48:13.720
Then why are you out here dancing and teasing other guys?

00:48:13.720 --> 00:48:17.400
Hey, what are you talking about? If you’re drunk, just go home and sleep.

00:48:20.120 --> 00:48:21.360
Let go of me. Now.

00:48:21.360 --> 00:48:23.960
Come home with me. Now.

00:48:23.960 --> 00:48:25.680
Damn it.

00:48:25.680 --> 00:48:28.520
If you’re sick, tell your family to get you checked.

00:48:28.520 --> 00:48:30.840
Not come out here and harass everyone like this.

00:48:30.840 --> 00:48:32.200
Let go.

00:48:34.400 --> 00:48:37.320
You’re the one. If you’re drunk, stop rambling.

00:48:37.640 --> 00:48:39.160
And you’re coming home with me. Now.

00:48:40.600 --> 00:48:44.920
The moment alcohol hits your lips,
where does that ‘good girl’ image you try so hard to keep go?

00:48:46.120 --> 00:48:48.120
Just look at yourself right now.

00:48:49.000 --> 00:48:53.920
I was gone for less than a day, and you were already so pent-up
you had to go out and flirt with other guys?

00:49:01.720 --> 00:49:03.720
This slap is for your filthy mouth.

00:49:07.680 --> 00:49:09.680
A filthy mouth?

00:49:23.960 --> 00:49:27.760
Next time, keep your disgusting behavior to yourself.

00:49:28.360 --> 00:49:31.240
No matter how rich you are, or how good-looking you think you are

00:49:31.400 --> 00:49:33.400
Not every woman is going to put up with you.

00:50:08.640 --> 00:50:10.640
P'Flint, you’re back already?

00:50:12.600 --> 00:50:14.600
Is this how you behave when I’m not around?

00:50:16.000 --> 00:50:18.000
Me...? What did I do, P'Flint?

00:50:20.960 --> 00:50:22.960
What did you do?

00:50:43.000 --> 00:50:45.000
Please let me go, P'Flint.

00:50:50.320 --> 00:50:52.320
Please let me go.

00:50:54.440 --> 00:50:58.240
P'Flint, what’s wrong? Why are you doing this?

00:50:58.240 --> 00:51:00.440
Don’t pretend like you’ve never done this before.

00:51:00.800 --> 00:51:03.960
But when you go out at night and end up going up to some guy’s condo

00:51:04.280 --> 00:51:06.280
You have no shame at all.

00:51:15.800 --> 00:51:17.240
Why?

00:51:17.720 --> 00:51:19.720
Or is it different when you do it with other people?

00:51:21.480 --> 00:51:23.080
Fine.

00:51:24.000 --> 00:51:25.680
Then I'll do it.

00:51:30.600 --> 00:51:32.040
P'Flint!

00:51:43.800 --> 00:51:48.600
If that’s what it takes for you to trust me, then go ahead.

00:52:21.640 --> 00:52:23.640
Why didn’t you answer the phone?

00:52:41.760 --> 00:52:43.240
What are you doing?

00:52:43.480 --> 00:52:45.480
Why didn’t you answer the phone?

00:53:24.480 --> 00:53:26.080
Dear, dairy.

00:53:26.600 --> 00:53:29.320
P'Flint dropped me off at the airport today.

00:53:29.960 --> 00:53:32.160
I never thought she’d come.

00:53:33.320 --> 00:53:37.320
The airport was crowded and so noisy.

00:53:37.560 --> 00:53:41.680
But no matter what, P'Flint always stands out in my heart.

00:53:41.960 --> 00:53:43.960
‘Study hard,’

00:53:44.400 --> 00:53:48.160
just a simple sentence yet I remember it so clearly.

00:53:52.400 --> 00:53:54.840
If you’re so sure that I’m the one at fault,

00:53:55.320 --> 00:53:57.320
then what do you still want from me?

00:53:59.160 --> 00:54:03.440
About those leaked photos of the two of you going up to the condo
and the ones in the news… what’s really going on? Could you tell me?

00:54:04.440 --> 00:54:07.640
But everything I did… it was because I was worried about you, Sun.

00:54:09.640 --> 00:54:11.200
Let's go home.

00:54:11.200 --> 00:54:13.080
In what way are you worried about me?

00:54:17.400 --> 00:54:18.920
Sun, can you listen to me first?

00:54:20.680 --> 00:54:22.280
(Even if you’ve never seen me, there’s never been a day when I didn’t see you.)

00:54:22.280 --> 00:54:26.080
(Even if you’ve never seen me, there’s never been a day when I didn’t see you.)
- Some types of sasaeng fans just want attention from the artists.

00:54:26.440 --> 00:54:29.720
They don’t care whether that attention is right or wrong.

00:54:30.480 --> 00:54:33.160
Then what should we do, P’Flint?

00:54:34.880 --> 00:54:37.680
Sun Atita.